-- BJM, Investec, Naspers and Old Mutual: South African Stock Market Preview
-- Janice Kew
-- 2010-06-18T05:32:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/bjm-investec-naspers-and-old-mutual-south-african-stock-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  
 South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  advanced for
a third trading day, climbing 116.31, or 0.4 percent, to
27,799.03.  
 Barnard Jacobs Mellet Holdings Ltd.  (BJM SJ): The brokerage
that last month agreed to sell its securities unit to
Renaissance Capital said it has started talks that may affect
its share price. The stock slid 20 cents, or 5 percent, to 3.80
rand.  
 Investec Plc  (INL SJ): German Chancellor  Angela Merkel  said
that all 27 European Union members agreed to bank stress tests,
with the results of the stress tests to be published “at the
latest the second half of July.” Investec, the investment and
private bank, fell 40 cents, or 0.7 percent, to 57 rand.  
 Naspers Ltd.  (NPN SJ): Africa’s biggest media company said
annual profit fell by 40 percent to 50 percent from a year
earlier when the sale of a pay-television unit in Greece boosted
earnings. Naspers added 75 cents, or 0.3 percent, to 272.25
rand.  
 Old Mutual Plc  (OML SJ): Old Mutual Investment Group South
Africa said it appointed  Diane Radley , the finance director of
Old Mutual South Africa, as chief executive officer. Old Mutual
added 4 cents, or 0.3 percent, to 12.74 rand.  
 Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  
 Anglo American Plc (AAUK US) fell 0.5 percent to $19.78.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) added 2.6 percent to $44.80. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) fell 0.3 percent to $56.89. DRDGold Ltd.
(DROOY US) gained 3.4 percent to $4.51. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) retreated 2.3 percent to $12.72. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) added 2.4 percent to $10.15. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) climbed almost 2 percent to $26.20. Sappi Ltd. (SPP
US) shed 1 percent to $4. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) rose 1.1 percent
to $38.22.  
 -- With assistance from  Nicky Smith  in Johannesburg. Editors:
